  <span id="freeText3569245533626107812" style="display:none">The 'dreamer' aspect left me completely cold. But I've enjoyed following Bán/Valerius through the whole tetralogy. He seemed to me to have the most character development. Boudica's revolt and final battle were both VERY exciting. I could visualize the whole scene. Boudica's end as told in this novel sounded much more plausible than Tacitus's saying she poisoned herself. The author has a gift for descriptive prose. I realize she played with history, but it irritated me she located both Lugdunum and Canovium in Britannia. Lugdunum was the Roman name for Lyons in France, and Canovium that of Caerhun in Gwynedd [N. Wales]. <br /></span>
