      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Leanne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Leanne" href="/user/show/4752112-leanne">Leanne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer305815074" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13302403898892214777">Would have been 4 stars but the extra is for Valerius and Corvus by the river. Yep I cried at that (just a little bit). Their final meeting in battle wasn&apos;t as intense and heart-wrenching as it could&apos;ve been, but I suppose it was Boudica&apos;s story, not Valerius&apos;. More&apos;s the pity, such a great character.<br/><br/>Also noticed Scott left out some of the more grisly parts of the sacking of the Roman cities, like cutting off women&apos;s breasts and sowing them to their mouths. I suppose this could make readers empa</span>
  <span id="freeText13302403898892214777" style="display:none">Would have been 4 stars but the extra is for Valerius and Corvus by the river. Yep I cried at that (just a little bit). Their final meeting in battle wasn't as intense and heart-wrenching as it could've been, but I suppose it was Boudica's story, not Valerius'. More's the pity, such a great character.<br /><br />Also noticed Scott left out some of the more grisly parts of the sacking of the Roman cities, like cutting off women's breasts and sowing them to their mouths. I suppose this could make readers empathise less with Boudica, but similar done to men. Difference I suppose is men were soldiers, women were just helpless Roman females.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13302403898892214777" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


