<div id="review_2613819425" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2613819425" />
    <a title="Moriquen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/65941941-moriquen"><img alt="Moriquen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1542969780p2/65941941.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2613819425?book_show_action=true">Jan 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Moriquen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Moriquen" href="/user/show/65941941-moriquen">Moriquen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2613819425" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1760592006762354773">Again I felt this was a wonderful read and I feel sorry that this is the end of the series. Throughout the book Scott manages to keep you hoping to a different ending then the one history dictates. And although she takes a lot of liberties the ending feels right for the characters she has built so far.<br/>The only downside is that I sometimes was a little bit confused when old and new characters came together. I had this feeling before in one of the other volumes, but now I felt that regularly I cou</span>
  <span id="freeText1760592006762354773" style="display:none">Again I felt this was a wonderful read and I feel sorry that this is the end of the series. Throughout the book Scott manages to keep you hoping to a different ending then the one history dictates. And although she takes a lot of liberties the ending feels right for the characters she has built so far.<br />The only downside is that I sometimes was a little bit confused when old and new characters came together. I had this feeling before in one of the other volumes, but now I felt that regularly I couldn't remember who a certain character was, what he or she looked like or how we first met them.<br />But in short I still love the book and I'm sad to have come to the ending of it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1760592006762354773" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


